<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">How to Use EV Score in Practice</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Before every play:</span> Check your rack's EV Score on ScrabbleWordsFinder. Enter your tiles and the EV appears instantly next to the results. If it's below 30, consider whether exchanging might be better than playing a low-scoring word.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Compare leaves:</span> When choosing between two plays, check the EV of the tiles you'd leave behind. A play scoring 28 points with a 65 EV leave is often better than a play scoring 32 points with a 25 EV leave.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Track your averages:</span> Tournament players aim for an average rack EV of 55-65 across a game. If your average drops below 45, you're making plays that leave bad letters behind.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Top Bingo Stems That Boost EV</h2>

<p>The algorithm awards bonus points when your rack contains 5-6 letters from these proven bingo stems:</p>

<div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SATIRE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">97 bingos</span></span>
